ress Formula Tablets is Australia’s No1 Stress Formula*providing nutrients beneficial in times of ongoing stress.","descriptionTh":null,"extractedText":"Blackmores Executive B Stress Formula Tablets All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Executive B Stress Formula Size Size 28 tablets 62 tablets 160 tablets Good health changes everything—support your energy and stress needs with Blackmores Executive B Stress Formula. This comprehensive formula combines B-group vitamins and minerals to support healthy stress response in the body, maintain energy production, and support general mental wellbeing. It also helps support nervous system function and assist neurotransmitter synthesis when dietary intake is inadequate. Designed for people experiencing lifestyle or work-related stress, this formulation helps relieve tiredness, supports energy production and stress response throughout the day. Taken twice daily, it offers targeted support for everyday mental and physical demands. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Stress Nervous System Health Energy Halal Certified No Added Yeast No Added Dairy Benefits & How To Use Benefits Supports healthy stress response in the body. Supports nervous system function and health. Supports energy levels and production. Relieves fatigue and feelings of weakness. Supports mental focus and clarity. Supports general health and wellbeing. Dosage Adults 19 years and older Take 1 tablet two times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. WARNING - Stop taking this medication if you experience tingling, burning or numbness and see your healthcare practitioner as soon as possible [Contains vitamin B6]. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Dietary supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. Vitamin B2 (riboflavin) supplements may change urine colour to bright yellow. This is harmless and temporary. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains gluten, sulfites and soya bean products. Contains 67.4mg of potassium. Benefits Dosage Warnings Supports healthy stress response in the body. Supports nervous system function and health. Supports energy levels and production. Relieves fatigue and feelings of weakness. Supports mental focus and clarity. Supports general health and wellbeing. Adults 19 years and older Take 1 tablet two times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. WARNING - Stop taking this medication if you experience tingling, burning or numbness and see your healthcare practitioner as soon as possible [Contains vitamin B6]. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Dietary supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. Vitamin B2 (riboflavin) supplements may change urine colour to bright yellow. This is harmless and temporary. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains gluten, sulfites and soya bean products. Contains 67.4mg of potassium. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Thiamine hydrochloride 75 mg equivalent thiamine (vitamin B1) 66.9 mg Riboflavin (vitamin B2) 10 mg Nicotinamide 100 mg Calcium pantothenate 75 mg equivalent pantothenic acid 68.8 mg Pyridoxine hydrochloride 25 mg equivalent pyridoxine (vitamin B6) 20.6 mg Cyanocobalamin (vitamin B12) 30 micrograms Biotin 20 micrograms Calcium ascorbate dihydrate 145.5 mg equivalent ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 120 mg Ascorbic acid 130 mg Total vitamin C 250 mg d-alpha-tocopheryl acid succinate 41.3 mg equivalent vitamin E 50 IU Magnesium phosphate pentahydrate 140 mg equivalent magnesium 28.9 mg Calcium phosphate 95.6 mg equivalent calcium 37 mg Monobasic potassium phosphate 117 mg equivalent potassium 33.7 mg Folic acid 150 micrograms Avena sativa (oats) extract dry conc. 25 mg equivalent dry seed 250 mg Passiflora incarnata (passion flower) extract dry co