for family members aged 2 years and over. Kaloba® is well-tolerated and offers a natural option for managing respiratory symptoms. Always read the label and follow usage guidance. Product Format Liquid Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Respiratory Health Sinusitis No Added Soya Bean Benefits & How To Use Benefits Helps reduce recovery time and symptoms of acute bronchitis For the treatment of acute sinusitis. Features children&#x27;s doses* for acute bronchitis Well-tolerated and suitable for family members over 2 years old with acute bronchitis*. Convenient drop dosage. AUST-R registered complementary medicine. *Children under the age of 6 years should only be treated with Kaloba® after previous consultation with a doctor. Dosage Acute bronchitis Adults and adolescents over the age of 12 years - Take 30 drops (1.35 mL) 3 times a day. Children aged between 6-12 years - Take 20 drops (0.9 mL) 3 times a day. Children aged between 2-5 years - Give 10 drops (0.45 mL) 3 times a day. Acute sinusitis Adults - Take 60 drops (2.7 ml) 3 times a day. The correct dosage can be taken straight from a spoon or mixed with half a glass of water. The entire contents of the glass should be drink straight away. Take one dose in the morning, midday and evening. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Consult a doctor immediately if the condition does not improve within one week, in case of fever lasting for several days or in case of shortness of breath or if you cough up bloody sputum. Kaloba® should not be used in children under 2 years of age. Children under the age of 6 years should only be treated with Kaloba® after previous consultation with your doctor. Use during pregnancy or breast feeding is not recommended without first consulting with your doctor or pharmacist. Treatment duration should not exceed 1 week for acute bronchitis and 3 weeks for acute sinusitis. Contains 12% alcohol. B