olic Tablets All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores I-Folic™ Size Size 150 tablets Good health changes everything - start your pregnancy journey with Blackmores I-Folic™. This convenient one-a-day formula combines folic acid and iodine to help support healthy foetal development, including the development of the brain and central nervous system. Taken daily, it also helps prevent neural tube defects such as spina bifida and anencephaly when taken preconception and in early pregnancy. I-Folic™ is ideal for women planning a pregnancy or in the early stages of pregnancy and comes in a small, easy-to-swallow tablet. With a five-month supply per bottle, it’s a simple way to support a healthy start for both mum and baby. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Foetal Development Pregnancy Health Women&#x27;s Health Halal Certified No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy No Added Soya Bean Benefits & How To Use Benefits Provides a daily dose of 500 microgram of folic acid that may reduce the risk of birth defects of the brain & / or spinal cord such as spina bifida if taken daily for 1 month prior to conception and during pregnancy. Provides iodine for the development of baby&#x27;s brain, visual, motor skills & hearing. Maintains folic acid and iodine levels. One bottle will provide you with a 5-month supply of these two essential nutrients. Dosage Adults Take 1 tablet with a meal, or as prescribed by a health professional. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Do not exceed the stated dose of folic acid. If you have had a baby with neural tube defect/spina bifida, seek specific medical advice. Always talk to your health professional before taking multiple products for pregnancy. Supplements may only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. Advise your doctor of any medicine you take during pregnancy, particularly in your first trimester. Not to be taken with Blackmores Conceive Well Gold, Blackmores Pregnancy & Breast-Feeding Gold, Blackmores Folate, or other folic acid containing supplements. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products. Benefits Dosage Warnings Provides a daily dose of 500 microgram of folic acid that may reduce the risk of birth defects of the brain & / or spinal cord such as spina bifida if taken daily for 1 month prior to conception and during pregnancy. Provides iodine for the development of baby&#x27;s brain, visual, motor skills & hearing. Maintains folic acid and iodine levels. One bottle will provide you with a 5-month supply of these two essential nutrients. Adults Take 1 tablet with a meal, or as prescribed by a health professional. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Do not exceed the stated dose of folic acid. If you have had a baby with neural tube defect/spina bifida, seek specific medical advice. Always talk to your health professional before taking multiple products for pregnancy. Supplements may only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. Advise your doctor of any medicine you take during pregnancy, particularly in your first trimester. Not to be taken with Blackmores Conceive Well Gold, Blackmores Pregnancy & Breast-Feeding Gold, Blackmores Folate, or other folic acid containing supplements. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products. Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Folic acid 500 micrograms Potassium iodide 196.2 micrograms eqivalent iodine 150 micrograms I-Folic™ Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education Our Brands & Product