  ('9be55bac-8f3c-4a10-97fe-43c5901c4d26'::uuid, '131fab35-0a0b-4d39-9c2e-7c57aecaebfa'::uuid, null, 'product_updated', 'codex_blackmores_clean_approval', '{"id":"131fab35-0a0b-4d39-9c2e-7c57aecaebfa","title":"Blackmores Follow-on Formula","region":"TH","source":"manufacturer_import","status":"pending_review","brand_id":"40e4806a-5049-4668-8d29-ab36a31202dd","category":null,"currency":"THB","platform":"manual","title_en":"Blackmores Follow-on Formula","title_th":null,"image_url":"https://images.contentstack.io/v3/assets/blt948bd74310fc0ad0/bltbe83ff8b0b9ebec5/68bfb78677db246b10a5fda5/9300807358252-1.webp","brand_name":"blackmores","created_at":"2026-05-21T13:09:45.667399+00:00","source_url":"https://www.blackmores.com.au/products/follow-on-formula","updated_at":"2026-05-21T13:09:45.685845+00:00","admin_notes":null,"description":"Blackmores Follow-on Infant Formula is developed to meet the nutrition needs of infants aged 6–12 months.","product_url":"https://www.blackmores.com.au/products/follow-on-formula","label_status":"parsed","price_amount":null,"product_kind":"multi","description_en":"Blackmores Follow-on Infant Formula is developed to meet the nutrition needs of infants aged 6–12 months.","description_th":null,"normalized_url":"https://www.blackmores.com.au/products/follow-on-formula","current_version":1,"fda_verified_at":null,"price_cached_at":null,"source_snapshot":{"dosage":"for use. Read the","locale":"en","parser":"blackmores_structured_ingredients_v2","titleEn":"Blackmores Follow-on Formula","htmlLength":222502,"validation":{"status":"pass","reasons":[],"summary":"24 matchable canonical facts.","checkedAt":"2026-05-21T13:09:45.682Z","matchableFactCount":24},"description":"Blackmores Follow-on Infant Formula is developed to meet the nutrition needs of infants aged 6–12 months.","descriptionEn":"Blackmores Follow-on Infant Formula is developed to meet the nutrition needs of infants aged 6–12 months.","descriptionTh":null,"extractedText":"Blackmores Follow-on Formula All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Follow-on Formula Size Size 900 grams Blackmores Follow-On Formula is made with premium Australian cow’s milk and enriched with carefully balanced nutrients to support your baby’s next stage of growth and development. Nutritionally complete for babies from 6 to 12 months, it is designed to complement a varied diet as your baby grows. Product Format Powder Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Infant & Toddler Nutrition Halal Certified No Added Gluten No Added Wheat Benefits & How To Use Benefits Blackmores Follow-on Formula is nutritionally complete to meet the nutritional needs of formula feeding babies. Enriched with a special blend of nutrients suitable for infants from 6 to 12 months. Made from premium fresh Australian milk from cows in the lush pastures of Australia. Comprehensive formula using high quality ingredients. GMO Free. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Follow instructions exactly. Prepare bottles and teats as directed. Do not change proportions of powder except on medical advice. Incorrect preparation can make your baby very ill. This infant formula product should not be used for infants under the age of 6 months. It is recommended that infants from the age of 6 months should be offered foods in addition to the infant formula. CONTAINS MILK AND SOY. MAY CONTAIN FISH. Feeding Guide FEEDING GUIDE - TO PREPARE ONE FEED Age of infant Cooled boiled water (mL) Level Scoops of Formula Formula Feeds per Day 6 - 12 months 180 mL 3 4-5 One level scoop = 8.8 g of formula. HOW TO PREPARE Wash hands and all equipment before preparing formula. Sterilise all equipment by boiling for five minutes or by using an approved steriliser. Boil fresh drinking water for five minutes and leave to cool. When cool, measure the required amount of water and formula by consulting the feeding guide on the product label. Using only the scoop provided, lightly fill one measurement of the powder and use levelling blade on tin. Pour the powder into the prepared water, cap the bottle and shake until the powder is dissolved. Check the formula temperature on your wrist then feed immediately. Always prepare each bottle separately and freshly for every feed. Discard unused portions; do not keep for later feeding. Benefits Warnings Feeding Guide Blackmores Follow-on Formula is nutritionally complete to meet the nutritional needs of formula feeding babies. Enriched with a special blend of nutrients suitable for infants from 6 to 12 months. Made from premium fresh Australian milk from cows in the lush pastures of Australia. Comprehensive formula using high quality ingredients. GMO Free. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Follow instructions exactly. Prepare bottles and teats as directed. Do not change proportions of powder except on medical advice. Incorrect preparation can make your baby very ill. This infant formula product should not be used for infants under the age of 6 months. It is recommended that infants from the age of 6 months should be offered foods in addition to the infant formula. CONTAINS MILK AND SOY. MAY CONTAIN FISH. FEEDING GUIDE - TO PREPARE ONE FEED Age of infant Cooled boiled water (mL) Level Scoops of Formula Formula Feeds per Day 6 - 12 months 180 mL 3 4-5 One level scoop = 8.8 g of formula. HOW TO PREPARE Wash hands and all equipment before preparing formula. Sterilise all equipment by boiling for five minutes or by using an approved steriliser. Boil fresh drinking water for five minutes and leave to cool. When cool, measure the required amount of water and formula by consulting the feeding guide on the product label. Using only the scoop provided, lightly fill one measurement of the powder and use levelling blade on tin. Pour the powder into the prepared water, cap the bottle and shake until the powder is dissolved. Check the formula temperature on your wrist then feed immediately. Always prepare each bottle separately and freshly for every feed. Discard unused portions; do not keep for later feeding. The Blackmores Difference Nutritional Information Average Quantity per 100 mL of Prepared Formula Energy 270 kJ Protein 2.20 g Fat, total 3.12 g Linoleic Acid 0.38 g alpha-linolenic Acid (ALA) 43.6 mg Docosahexaenoic Acid (DHA) 5.94 mg Arachidonic Acid (ARA) 5.94 mg Carbohydrate 6.67 g Dietary fibre, total 0.46 g Galacto-oligosaccharide (GOS) 0.46 g Sodium 26.4 mg Potassium 79.2 mg Chloride 62.7 mg Vitamins Vitamin A 50.0 µg RE Vitamin D 0.86 µg Vitamin E 0.99 mg α-TE Vitamin K1 5.28 µg Thiamin (vitamin B1) 66.0 µg Riboflavin (vitamin B2) 198 µg Vitamin B6 52.8 µg Vitamin B12 0.33 µg Niacin (vitamin B3) 0.48 mg Folate 13.2 µg Pantothenic Acid (vitamin B5) 356 µg Vitamin C 9.90 mg Biotin 1.98 µg Minerals Copper 52.8 µg Magnesium 7.26 mg Iron 0.90 mg Zinc 0.38 mg Manganese 10.6 µg Calcium 68.6 mg Phosphorous 42.2 mg Iodine 9.24 µg Selenium 1.98 µg Others Inositol 3.96 mg Taurine 5.28 mg Nucleotides 3.30 mg CMP 1.30 mg AMP 0.81 mg UMP 0.65 mg IMP 0.36 mg GMP 0.18 mg Lutein 5.94 µg Ingredients Milk Solids, Vegetable Oil Blend ( Soy ), Galacto-oligosaccharide (GOS) ( Milk ), Emulsifier ( Soy Lecithin), Arachidonic Acid Oil (ARA) ( Milk ), Docosahexaenoic Acid Oil (DHA) ( Milk ), Nucleotides (5`-CMP, 5`-AMP, di Sodium 5`-UMP, di Sodium 5`-IMP, di Sodium 5`-GMP), Taurine, Inositol, Antioxidants (Ascorbyl Palmitate, Tocopherol Concentrate, Mixed), Lutein. Minerals (Calcium Carbonate, Potassium Chloride, di Sodium Phosphate, Magnesium Chloride, Potassium Hydroxide, tri Calcium Phosphate, Ferric Pyrophosphate, Manganese Sulphate, Zinc Sulphate, Copper Sulphate, Sodium Selenite, Potassium Iodide). Vitamins (Sodium Ascorbate (vitamin C), d-alpha Tocopheryl Acetate (vitamin E) ( Soy ), Retinyl Acetate (vitamin A), Nicotinamide (vitamin B3), Calcium Pantothenate (vitamin B5), Cyanocobalamin (vitamin B12), D-Biotin, Folic Acid (vitamin B9), Riboflavin (vitamin B2), Thiamin Hydrochloride (vitamin B1), Pyridoxine Hydrochloride (vitamin B6), Phytonadione (vitamin K1) ( Soy ), Cholecalciferol (vitamin D)). CONTAINS MILK AND SOY. MAY CONTAIN FISH. Frequently asked questions about Follow-on Formula How can I learn more about the Blackmores Infant Nutrition Range? You can learn more about the range and read our FAQs here . Alternatively, contact our Naturopathic Advisory Team on 1800 803 760 . What is the main difference between Newborn (Stage 1) and Follow-on (Stage 2) formula? Newborn formula is suitable from birth and, for non-breastfed infants, can be a sole source of nutrition. A Follow-on formula is to be used from 6 months of age, around which time complementary foods start being introduced into the diet. These formulas are nutritionally adapted to the needs of the growing child. Do your formulas contain all the nutrients my baby needs until 12 months? Our Newborn Formula for 0 – 6 month olds and our Follow-on Formula for 6 to 12 month olds are nutritionally balanced, containing proteins from fresh cow’s milk and other essential nutrients that are age appropriate and meet the strict nutritional requirements identified by Food Standards Australia New Zealand (FSANZ). If you require further information and for individual advice, please consult your healthcare professional. Can my baby have more or less feeds than is indicated on the feeding guide? Follow the instructions for preparing the bottle as directed on the container. The feeding guide will give the proportions of the powder required. Incorrect preparation can make your baby very ill so always follow instructions on pack. Each baby’s nutritional needs and appetite vary from baby to baby and day to day. As a carer you will learn to read the signs your baby makes when he/she is hungry. If you are unsure about the feeding requirements of your baby, you should check with your health care professional. How do I prepare my baby’s formula? Please look at both methods detailed below and choose the one that is best for your family. If you are unable to reliably store your baby’s formula in cool, dry conditions, your baby has health issues or was born prematurely, please consider using the hot water preparation with water no cooler than 70°C. Preparing formula with hot water Preparing formula with cooled water Preparing formula with cooled water (Vietnamese) The WHO and other many other health advisory bodies advise that best practice is to boil the kettle and allow it to cool for just under half an hour to reach approximately 70°C. You then add the powder to the water and can cool the prepared milk down to feeding temperature quickly by running the bottle under the cold water tap or placing in a jug of cool water. Please be sure to check that the milk has cooled down to the right temperature before you feed your baby. It should feel just slightly warm on your skin. How long can the product be used once opened? We recommend you use the contents of the tin within 4 weeks of opening. Follow-on Formula Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam Terms & Policies Privacy Policy & Practices Terms Of Purchase Terms of Service Posting Guidelines Social Media House Rules Terms & Policies Privacy Policy & Practices Terms Of Purchase Terms of Service Posting Guidelines Social Media House Rules Contacts & FAQs Report a Suspected Adverse Experience Contact Us Ask a Naturopath Product & Purchasing FAQs Blackmores Subscribe Contacts & FAQs Report a Suspected Adverse Experience Contact Us Ask a Naturopath Product & Purchasing FAQs Blackmores Subscribe Back To Top Terms of Purchase Privacy Pol","productImportId"