onTh":null,"extractedText":"Blackmores Folate Tablets All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Folate Size Size 90 tablets Blackmores Folate provides 500 micrograms of folic acid in a convenient, once-daily tablet. This essential nutrient is used to support healthy pregnancy, help prevent neural tube defects such as spina bifida, and maintain healthy foetal development. It also assists in healthy red blood cell production and supports preconception health. Ideal for women planning pregnancy, this formula ensures reliable folic acid intake where dietary levels may be insufficient. Folic acid plays a crucial role in supporting cell growth and DNA synthesis, particularly in early pregnancy. Good health changes everything—support your pregnancy journey with Blackmores Folate. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For General Health Pregnancy Health Women&#x27;s Health No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy Benefits & How To Use Benefits Helps to prevent neural tube defects such as spina bifida when trying to conceive and during the first trimester of pregnancy. Maintains folic acid levels in the body. Assists healthy red blood cell production. Supports general health and wellbeing. Convenient one-a-day dosage. Dosage Adults Take 1 tablet a day with a meal, or as prescribed by a health professional. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Do not exceed the stated dose of folic acid except on medical advice. If you have had a baby with a neural tube defect/spina bifida, seek specific medical advice. Always talk to your health professional before taking multiple products for pregnancy. Advise your doctor of any medicine you take during pregnancy, particularly in the first trimester. Dietary supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products. Benefits Dosage Warnings Helps to prevent neural tube defects such as spina bifida when trying to conceive and during the first trimester of pregnancy. Maintains folic acid levels in the body. Assists healthy red blood cell production. Supports general health and wellbeing. Convenient one-a-day dosage. Adults Take 1 tablet a day with a meal, or as prescribed by a health professional. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Do not exceed the stated dose of folic acid except on medical advice. If you have had a baby with a neural tube defect/spina bifida, seek specific medical advice. Always talk to your health professional before taking multiple products for pregnancy. Advise your doctor of any medicine you take during pregnancy, particularly in the first trimester. Dietary supplements can only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains soya bean products. Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Folic acid 500 micrograms Folate Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam Terms & Policies Privacy Policy & Practices Terms Of Purchase Terms of Service Posting Guidelines Social Media House Rules Terms & Policies Privacy Policy & Practices Terms Of Purchase Terms of Service Posting Guidelines So